body:
Yes,

```
hSocketMax = max(hSocketMax, hListenSocket + 1);
...
hSocketMax = max(hSocketMax, pnode->hSocket + 1);
```

Then change the select line to (ie, remove the + 1)

```
    int nSelect = select(hSocketMax, &fdsetRecv, &fdsetSend, &fdsetError, &timeout);
```

And change this loop to < i.s.o <=:

```
            for (unsigned int i = 0; i < hSocketMax; i++)
                FD_SET(i, &fdsetRecv);
```

Only after that, you can check for hSocketMax==0 and be sure that it means "no sockets".

